reviews.review: Episode 9 has so many great moments that are reminiscent to past Star Wars films we all know and love. JJ Abrams provides answers to the questions that were left with us in The Last Jedi and ends the Skywalker Saga in the most fitting way possible. A must see for the avid Star Wars fan!

vast improvement over Force Awakens and Last Jedi. The story dived in to Jedi/Sith Cannon and lore that vastly enriched the story. Movie was more fluid and brought all the players together. Too many plot twists at the end.  Keep it simple i say.

Disney just ruined the larger than life saga of Skywalker

After 42 years, How bad how it has ended, They just took The Concept of Choosen One and threw it in the trash can, And force is just a normal tool now which everyone can use, So there is basically no such thing as force-sencitive anymore and if everybody chosen one then nobody is, 

They just wasted the whole role of Anakin
It's not a good movie but it's not a bad movie and it's Star Wars so...

After the dumpster fire the last Jedi was, J.J. Abrams did a remarkable job considering what he was left to work with. Per usual I saw critics lambasting this movie so I was cautiously optimistic I would enjoy it.

Not serious enough to ruin the experience for me but a little funny, it seems the directors signature lens flare has been traded in for the fake out! Lol

Sorry, but there was nothing hopeful about that ending. The last Skywalker dies? ! Neck-breaking pacing, retcons, damage to previous movie and lore, cringe moments and dialogue, weird story-telling decisions. Agree with the critics scores on this one. It could've been so much better.
It's a Christmas miracle!!!  Big thanks to JJ and the gang.
Lots of fan service, but a hugely entertaining final chapter

Pathetic. No other way to put it. JJ Abrams picks everything good from ep. VIII and throws it in the trash just to please some lunatic 'fans' that wouldn't be able to interpret a film to save their lives.

Honestly? Why would you completely retcon everything that happened in the previous two movies. While I admit some aspects of this movie were fun, I definitely did not leave the theater feel hopeful. I really didn't understand the back and fourth plot, how it seems every character arc backpedaled, and how just disappointing the whole movie was. A huge let down.
